description: The expert on the post-Soviet region has been held in Russia since June 2024. Sentenced to three years in a penal colony, he now faces up to 20 years in prison.

headline: Deadly Israeli strikes on Khan Yunis's Nasser Hospital spark outrage all the way to the White House
description: More than 20 people died on Monday, among them medical staff and five journalists. Benjamin Netanyahu was forced to express his regrets, while the Israeli military cited collateral damage. Yet the use of a 'double strike,' a tactic repeatedly employed since the start of the war, undermines that argument.

description: Established in 2017 near the Jordanian border, the Kedem Arava settlement contains prefabricated homes housing some 60 families, former city dwellers seeking a life closer to nature. While most residents deny ideological motivation, their presence fully aligns with the annexation of Palestinian territory sought by the Israeli far right.
